not overly hoppy so that the Vienna and Munich
malt flavor is more promenant. This beer is
typically higher in alcohol content than
traditional German lagers at around 5-6% abv. The
aroma is comparable to Vienna lager.
According to German Law, Oktoberfestbier is
legally reserved for the six breweries who are
allowed to serve their beer at the Munich
and Spaten. However, German Law does not extend
beyond the German borders so the
märzen/oktoberfest is used as a label for a beer
style elsewhere, particulary among craft brewers.
